Electronic display board installation at DEOCs;
	
		Support equipment, lifesaving materials, communication equipment to district EOCs (Kanchanpur, Bardiya, and Chitwan) for developing SoPs in line with NEOC SOPs;
	
		Support to NEOC/REOC (communication channel established and emergency telephone list preparation at NEOC/REOC, equipment support);
	
		Small scale mitigation work
	
		Exploration of Appropriate technology for installing landslide early warning;
	
		Preparation of VDC Disaster Risk Management Plan based on MOFALD Guideline;
	
		Supply of preparedness and response equipment (Life Jackets, Boats, Ropes, Tubes and storage facilities);
	
		Trainings to staffs and stakeholders (Advocacy and policy, LDRMP, technical training on Hydrological data analysis, GIS training, Landslide EWS, CBDRR including CBEWS, GSI, PwDs, mainstreaming  DRR into District Development Planning);
	
		Technical support to other organizations on EWS, LDRMP, DPRP (DDRCs/DDCs, NGOs, INGOs, UN);
	
		Support to DHM, DSCWM, MOFALD, and other concerned government agencies (Equipment, logistics, Team building, knowledge sharing on CBEWS);
	
		Materials support to DDRCs members for Search and Rescue training;
	
		Building capacity of NRCS to mainstream, assess, design and establish CBEWS;
	
		Support for implementation of CBEWS guideline;
	
		Design, drawing, cost estimate, and supervision small scale mitigation Work;
	
		Mock Drill and simulation exercise in communities;
	
		Support to district EWS (improving upstream linkages and verifying water level thresholds - upstream visits and meetings);
	
		EWS technical equipment (Hand operated sirens, Megaphones, CDMA Phones and storage facilities);
	
		Refresher training to task forces (First Aid and Search and Rescue);
	
		Awareness raising activities (Door to door - 2 times, wall paintings, visibility boards, song competitions, flyer publications) (School awareness)
	
		Activities for mainstreaming PwDs into DRR;
	
		Joint advocacies at key annual DM/DR events (IDDR Day, Earthquke safety day, others) Emergency fund at VDC and District level;
	
		Publication of knowledge and visibility materials;
	
		Surveys and Evaluation.
